[3]
Date: Fri 20 Jun 2003
From: "Michelle Abbott" <michelle.abbott@masta.org>
Source: MASTA Health Report, Fri 20 Jun 2003 [edited]

Thailand: 24 000 Cases Reported So Far This Year
------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Public Health have reported over 24 000 cases of dengue
fever so far this year (June 2003). The media previously reported over 800
cases of dengue fever in and around Bangkok (Jan 2003).
A number of tourists visiting Koh Phangan were amongst the cases reported
last year. This flu-like virus is transmitted by daytime biting mosquitoes.
Avoid mosquito bites, there is no vaccine.
--
"Michelle Abbott"
<michelle.abbott@masta.org>

