[8]
Date: Fri 20 Jun 2003
From: "Pablo Nart" <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: Saudi Press Agency, Mon 2 Jun 2003 [edited]
<http://www.spa.gov.sa/html/archive_e.asp?srcfile=86806&NDay=02/06/2003&wcat
g=0>

Laos: Outbreak of Dengue Fever in Vientiane
-------------------------------------------
BANGKOK: An epidemic of dengue fever has killed seven people and about 1100
others have been infected by the disease in Vientiane, the capital of Laos,
the government-run radio reported on Mon 2 Jun 2003. Radio Vientiane said in
a report monitored in Bangkok that health officials were working to contain
the outbreak of the disease, which is characterized by painful joints, fever
and rash in its early stages. The radio report provided few details, saying
only that the seven fatal cases of the disease had occurred "recently"
