[9]
Date: Tue 17 Jun 2003
From: Marilda Milagres <milagres@fclnet.com.br>
Source: EPTV Campinas & EPTV Ribeirão, Mon 16 Jun 2003 (in Portuguese,
summary by Mod.JW) [edited]
<http://eptv.globo.com/noticias/1606200314507608.asp>

Brazil: Dengue Cases Escalate in Sao Paulo State
------------------------------------------------
In spite of the mass prevention campaign, the number of cases of dengue
reported in 2003 has already passed the total for 2002 in 2 cities in the
interior of Sao Paulo state, Hortolandia and Ribeirao Preto.
In Hortolandia, the number of cases of dengue was 112 in 2001, 59 in 2002,
and already 77 in the first 5 months of 2003. In Ribeirao Preto, the number
of cases has almost tripled, from 238 in 2002 to 715 already in 2003.

--
Marilda Milagres
<milagres@fclnet.com.br>
[According to PAHO provisional data so far in 2003 DEN-1, DEN-2 and DEN-3
have been associated with dengue hemorrhagic fever cases in Brazil
<http://www.paho.org/English/AD/DPC/CD/dengue-cases-2003.htm>. - Mod.CP]

