Source: La Prensa, Honduras, Sun 22 Jun 2003 (in Spanish, summary by Mod.JW)
[edited]
<http://www.laprensahn.com/nacionales.php?id=779&tabla=June_2003&fecha=20030
622>

Honduras: Total of Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever Deaths Rises to Nine
----------------------------------------------------------------
The Minister of Health, Elias Lizardo, confirmed the death of one person
from dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) in the township of Trinidad, Santa
Barbara. This brings to 9 the number of cases of DHF in 2003, 4 of them in
San Pedro Sula. The previous case was a 5-year-old child, who recovered.
People who do not clean up their vacant properties, or who have mosquitoes
breeding in their homes, will be fined.
During 2002, the Health Secretary recorded 3096 cases of dengue; in 2003,
2096 cases have been reported nationwide so far. But the peak of the
epidemic in 2002 fell in weeks 26-38 [July through September].
--
